One of the internal regulations of the company says that we will not announce any new service in advance, but only when it was already ready to work, which if it is certain is that the foreseeable problems of the coming months and years will be able to wreak havoc on the World: while some believe that the project of scanning and archive of books and magazines of Google will soon acquire such dimensions by the company.
And the fact that Google is going to create a genetic database will be able to provide a good raw material for science fiction writers, the Scroogled, a popular novel by Cory Doctorow, orwelianly describes that future, in which a man only from Google’s data can be described alarmingly well.
