Today the European Summit for Equal Opportunities has started in Paris, its host is France, which this year is also the turnout president of the European Union.
Lívia Járóka, Member of the European People’s Party for Fidesz, in her message to the plenary, as one of the main speakers of this professional meeting, drew attention to segregation in education, because it is one of the most serious violations that hit Roma children and is also the biggest obstacle to their interests.
This high-level conference was inaugurated - on behalf of the French Presidency - by Xavier Bertrand, French Minister for Employment and Social Affairs and Vladimir Spidla, European Commissioner for Employment, Social Affairs and Equal Opportunities.
