Students victims of expensive rent, up to 900 euros per room
The university rental market is unaware of the crisis.
According to the latest Sunia survey, the tenants’ union, renting a single room could cost a student 900 euros in Milan, 700 in Florence, 650 in Naples, 600 in Rome.
“The phenomenon has already assumed very serious characteristics to the point of excluding the right to study for a large proportion of young people due to the very high costs that the family would have to bear – explains Laura Mariani, head of the Sunia Studies Office – in these cities the strong demand has totally distorted the market to the point of triggering a process of widespread increase even for residents.”
Apart from that in most cases rental offers contain a number of violations: free type contracts, unregistered, no fee limit, sub-linked rentals.
Extraordinary interventions are necessary for Sunia, which, through the revision of the tax, can regulate prices.
Looking in detail at the survey, we see that in Milan, for a bed in Brianza area, they serve about 450 euros; for a single room from a minimum of 650 (Bande Nere area) to an average value of 800 (Lambiate area, Udine and Fiera area) to a maximum of 900 (in Victoria area).
In Florence a bed costs on average 350/400 euros, a room about 700.
In Bologna, where students concentrate in areas near the University, they serve 250/280 euros for a bed in a double room and from 370 to 500 euros for an individual.
In Rome in the central areas near the University (San Lorenzo, Piazza Bologna) you are asked about 600 euros for a single room and 450 for a bed in a double room.
Only slightly lower values (550 euros per single room) in areas near other Universities (Ostiense and Cinecittà).
Savings are made only if the peripheral area is changed: 300 euros for a bed and 450 euros for a single room in Prenestina, Centocelle and surrounding area.
In Naples for a bed you serve 300/450 euros, for a room you spend from 400 to 600 euros, with the highest prices in the areas Policlínico, Vomero and Colli Aminei.
